      <p>
        This manual establishes a working taxonomy for wrist-worn and portable field instruments inside Forgotten Industries. It is not a buying guide and not yet a dossier. It is a reference plate: a compact instrument used to compare cases, track acquisitions, preserve observed examples, and identify adjacent objects worthy of future archive records.
      </p>
      <p class="manual-question">What belongs on the wrist, in the pocket, or in the field bag of an archive built against forgetting?</p>
